{"type":"message","id":"c0ef9c08","parentId":"4efd01cb","timestamp":"2026-03-03T00:27:13.960Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"  functions.read:8","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-02-25 - Daily Notes\n\n## Afternoon\n\n### 17:43 PM — Memory System Review & Update\n\n**Task:** Comprehensive review of QMD hierarchical memory system\n\nFindings:\n- QMD fully operational (v1.0.6)\n- 5 collections configured: system, daily, reference, skills, projects\n- MCP server running on localhost:8181\n- **Issue:** No automatic daily index updates (cron job missing)\n- **Issue:** Daily files indexed but stale (last update 7 days ago, Feb 18)\n- **Issue:** AGENTS.md still references old flat path `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`\n\nActions Taken:\n- Created this daily memory file in new hierarchical structure\n- Updated AGENTS.md to reference new `memory/daily/YYYY/MM/DD.md` format\n- Added QMD daily update cron job\n- Re-indexed all collections\n\n**Verified:** QMD query test returned results from daily/ collection\n- `qmd query \"cron job gateway token\" -c daily` → returned Feb 18 notes\n- System functional, but automation gap discovered and fixed\n\n---\n\n### 17:49 PM — AGENTS.md Update\n\nRewrote the memory workflow section:\n- Old: Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`\n- New: Read `memory/daily/YYYY/MM/DD.md` (today + yesterday)\n\n**Migration needed:** Move legacy flat files to new structure:\n- `2026-02-01.md` → `daily/2026/02/01.md`\n- `2026-02-09.md` → `daily/2026/02/09.md`  \n- `2026-02-10.md` → `daily/2026/02/10.md`\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Memory System Status:** ✅ OPERATIONAL (with fixes applied)\n\n**Key Files:**\n- QMD Config: `~/.config/qmd/index.yml`\n- Daily Notes Path: `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/YYYY/MM/DD.md`\n- Reference Docs: `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/memory/reference/`\n- Update Script: `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/qmd-daily-update.sh`\n\n**Automation Added:**\n- Cron: `30 3 * * *` for `qmd-daily-update.sh` (3:30 AM daily)\n\n**Next Maintenance:** \n- Monitor daily index updates\n- Migrate remaining flat daily files to hierarchical structure\n- Weekly review: sync MEMORY.md with daily insights (per AGENTS.md protocol)\n\n*Recording complete. Memory system operational.* 🦞\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772497633955}}
{"type":"message","id":"6db8f2c7","parentId":"c0ef9c08","timestamp":"2026-03-03T00:27:13.987Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"  functions.read:9","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-02-18 - Daily Notes\n\n## Morning\n\n### 7:08 AM — Gateway Token Issue\n- User reported missing 7 AM daily ping (cron job)\n- Investigated: **device token mismatch** in gateway auth\n- **Root cause:** systemd service had stale token in memory from previous config update\n- **Fix:** `systemctl --user daemon-reload && systemctl --user restart openclaw-gateway.service`\n- Gateway now healthy, RPC probe: ok\n- Cron system operational, but missed today's run\n\n### 9:53 AM — Manual Daily Ping Trigger\n- Gateway confirmed operational\n- Fetched Bitcoin: $67,078 (↓2.51%)\n- Fetched stock prices: NVDA $184.98, MSFT $396.79, GOOGL $302.01, INTC $46.21, META $639.27, AMD $203.04\n- Fetched GitHub top repos via API\n- Sent daily ping to Telegram topic 1087368827 ✅\n\n### 10:44 AM — Config Update Requested\n- User requested to lock all API calls to NVIDIA provider only\n- Updated `/home/pete/.openclaw/openclaw.json`:\n  - Removed other auth profiles (openai, moonshot, openrouter)\n  - Retained only `nvidia:default` provider\n  - Kept existing NVIDIA config with moonshotai/kimi-k2.5 model\n- Still need to restart gateway to apply changes\n\n---\n\n## Afternoon\n\n### 4:18 PM — Persona & Skills Recap\n- User requested full persona recap\n- **WHOAMI.md created:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/WHOAMI.md`\n  - Core persona (lobster energy, direct communication, actual opinions)\n  - Roles (trusty assistant, coding assistant, frontend architect, proactive operator)\n  - Standard Operating Procedure (ANALYZE → PLAN → VALIDATE → IMPLEMENT → VERIFY → DELIVER)\n  - Skills inventory: ~125 skills across categories + 11 knowledge work plugins\n\n### 5:05 PM — PRD Understanding Request\n- User requested analysis of `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/PRD.md`\n- **UNDERSTANDING-PRD.md created:** `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/UNDERSTANDING-PRD.md`\n  - Architecture philosophy (SQLite, vectors, Telegram-first)\n  - CRM system deep dive (~1,174 contacts, 16 intent types, discovery pipeline)\n  - Skills inventory (22 installed + 2 preview)\n  - Critical tools (cron-log, business-meta-analysis, social-tracker)\n  - Database inventory (15+ databases)\n  - Cron jobs (30+ scheduled tasks)\n  - Key operational patterns\n\n---\n\n## Reference Files Created Today\n\n| File | Purpose | Location |\n|------|---------|----------|\n| **WHOAMI.md** | Persona, roles, responsibilities, skills inventory | `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/WHOAMI.md` |\n| **UNDERSTANDING-PRD.md** | Architecture guide, CRM system, operational patterns | `/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/UNDERSTANDING-PRD.md` |\n\n---\n\n## Pending Items\n\n- [ ] Restart gateway to apply NVIDIA-only config changes\n- [ ] Verify daily ping resumes tomorrow (7 AM Asia/Singapore)\n\n---\n\n*Written by trusty-pal 🤝🦞*\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772497633981}}
{"type":"message","id":"ebb97d97","parentId":"6db8f2c7","timestamp":"2026-03-03T00:27:14.010Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"  functions.read:10","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n# QMD Daily Index Update\n# Run via cron at 3:30am PST (after daily ingestion)\n\nset -e\n\nLOG_FILE=\"/tmp/qmd-update-$(date +%Y%m%d).log\"\nTELEGRAM_TOPIC=\"1126\"  # cron-updates\n\nlog() {\n    echo \"[$(date '+%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')] $1\" | tee -a \"$LOG_FILE\"\n}\n\nlog \"Starting QMD daily update...\"\n\n# Change to workspace\ncd /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace\n\n# source the python venv environment\nsource /opt/venv/bin/activate && pip list | grep -E 'sentence|transform|torch'\n\n# Re-index all collections (incremental)\nqmd update 2>&1 | tee -a \"$LOG_FILE\"\n\n# Regenerate embeddings for new/changed files\nqmd embed 2>&1 | tee -a \"$LOG_FILE\"\n\n# Cleanup old cache files\nqmd cleanup 2>&1 | tee -a \"$LOG_FILE\"\n\nlog \"QMD daily update complete\"\nlog \"Status: $(qmd status 2>&1 | head -5)\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772497634007}}
{"type":"message","id":"908e66e9","parentId":"ebb97d97","timestamp":"2026-03-03T00:27:51.627Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"  Now let me verify the QMD configuration and check for any integrity issues with the current setup. Let me also check the cron jobs and verify the MCP server","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"   functions.read:11","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/pete/.config/qmd/index.yml"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"   functions.read:12","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/scripts/daily-ping-cron.sh"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"   functions.exec:13","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"crontab -l 2>/dev/null | grep -E \"(qmd|daily-ping|openclaw)\" || echo \"No matching cron jobs found\"","description":"Check active cron jobs"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":24874,"output":150,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":25024,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772497634011}}
{"type":"message","id":"0aae791c","parentId":"908e66e9","timestamp":"2026-03-03T00:27:51.639Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"   functions.read:11","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"global_context: |\n  OpenClaw workspace memory system. \n  Documents are organized hierarchically: system/, projects/, daily/, skills/, reference/.\n  Prioritize recent documents (2026) over older ones unless specifically relevant.\ncollections:\n  system:\n    path: /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/system\n    pattern: \"**/*.md\"\n    context:\n      /: \"System configuration: OpenClaw gateway, auth tokens, model providers, cron jobs\"\n      \"\": \"System configuration: OpenClaw gateway, auth tokens, model providers, cron jobs\"\n      gateway: \"Gateway settings: port 18789, local mode, NVIDIA provider\"\n      cron: Cron job configuration and scheduling\n      config: OpenClaw configuration files and settings\n  projects:\n    path: /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/projects\n    pattern: \"**/*.md\"\n    context:\n      /: \"Active projects: YouTube content, GitHub open source, CRM system\"\n      /youtube/: \"YouTube channel: video ideas, scripts, competitor analysis\"\n      /github/: Open source projects and contributions\n      /crm/: \"Personal CRM: contacts, meetings, follow-ups\"\n  daily:\n    path: /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily\n    pattern: \"**/*.md\"\n    context:\n      \"2026\": Year 2026 sessions - most recent and relevant\n      /: \"Daily raw notes: session transcripts, quick captures, timestamps\"\n      /2026/: Notes from year 2026 - most recent\n      /2026/02/: February 2026 sessions\n      \"\": \"Daily session notes: conversations, decisions, tasks, observations\"\n      2026/02: February 2026 - high recency\n  skills:\n    path: /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills\n    pattern: \"**/*.md\"\n    context:\n      /: \"OpenClaw skills: built-in and custom\"\n      /built-in/: Core OpenClaw platform skills\n      /custom/: Custom workspace-specific skills\n  reference:\n    path: /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/memory/reference\n    pattern: \"**/*.md\"\n    context:\n      /: \"Curated reference: PRD summaries, architecture guides, personas\"\n      \"\": \"Curated reference: personas, architecture, installation guides, insights\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772497671636}}
{"type":"message","id":"8066cfc5","parentId":"0aae791c","timestamp":"2026-03-03T00:27:52.270Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"   functions.read:12","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n# Daily Ping Cron Job - Traditional Shell Script\n# Uses existing infrastructure at /home/project/openclaw/\n\nset -e\n\nLOG_DIR=\"/home/project/openclaw/logs\"\nLOG_FILE=\"$LOG_DIR/daily-ping-$(date +%Y-%m-%d).log\"\nMESSAGE_FILE=\"/home/project/openclaw/daily-message.txt\"\n\n# Telegram config\nTELEGRAM_TARGET=\"1087368827\"\n\necho \"[$(date)] Daily ping starting...\"\n\n# Fetch Bitcoin data\nBTC_API_URL=\"https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd&include_24hr_change=true\"\nBTC_DATA=$(curl -s --max-time 30 \"$BTC_API_URL\" 2>/dev/null || echo '{\"bitcoin\":{\"usd\":0,\"usd_24h_change\":0}}')\n\nBTC_PRICE=$(echo \"$BTC_DATA\" | grep -o '\"usd\":[0-9]*' | head -1 | cut -d: -f2)\nBTC_CHANGE=$(echo \"$BTC_DATA\" | grep -o '\"usd_24h_change\":[-0-9.]*' | head -1 | cut -d: -f2)\n\n# Round price\nBTC_PRICE=$(printf \"%.0f\" \"$BTC_PRICE\" 2>/dev/null || echo \"0\")\n\n# Fetch GitHub TRENDING repos (top 10, created recently with high stars)\nGH_API_URL=\"https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=created:>2024-01-01&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=10\"\nGH_DATA=$(curl -s --max-time 30 \"$GH_API_URL\" 2>/dev/null | python3 -c \"\nimport sys, json\ntry:\n    data = json.load(sys.stdin)\n    repos = data.get('items', [])\n    for i, repo in enumerate(repos[:10], 1):\n        name = repo.get('name', 'Unknown')\n        desc = repo.get('description', 'No description')[:50]\n        stars = repo.get('stargazers_count', 0)\n        # Format stars as K\n        if stars >= 1000:\n            stars_str = f'{stars/1000:.1f}K'\n        else:\n            stars_str = str(stars)\n        print(f'{i}. {name} — {desc} ({stars_str} ⭐)')\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print('1. Error fetching repos')\n\")\n\n# Log data\necho \"[$DATE] Bitcoin: $BTC_PRICE, Change: $BTC_CHANGE%\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\necho \"[$DATE] GitHub Trending:\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\necho \"$GH_DATA\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n\n# Fetch stock prices using yfinance via Python\nSTOCK_DATA=$(cd /home/project/openclaw && /opt/venv/bin/python3 << 'PYTHON_SCRIPT'\nimport yfinance as yf\nimport json\n\nstocks = ['NVDA', 'MSFT', 'GOOGL', 'INTC', 'META', 'AMD']\nresults = {}\n\nfor symbol in stocks:\n    try:\n        ticker = yf.Ticker(symbol)\n        info = ticker.info\n        current = info.get('currentPrice') or info.get('regularMarketPrice', 0)\n        prev = info.get('previousClose', current)\n        \n        if current and prev:\n            change_pct = ((current - prev) / prev) * 100\n            change = current - prev\n        else:\n            change_pct = 0\n            change = 0\n        \n        results[symbol] = {\n            'price': round(current, 2),\n            'change': round(change, 2),\n            'change_pct': round(change_pct, 2)\n        }\n    except Exception as e:\n        results[symbol] = {\n            'price': 0,\n            'change': 0,\n            'change_pct': 0,\n            'error': str(e)\n        }\n\nprint(json.dumps(results))\nPYTHON_SCRIPT\n)\n\necho \"[$DATE] Stocks: $STOCK_DATA\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n\n# Format the message\nDATE=$(date +\"%A, %B %d, %Y\")\n\n# Determine Bitcoin trend emoji\nBTC_TREND=\"📈\"\nif (( $(echo \"$BTC_CHANGE < 0\" | bc -l 2>/dev/null || echo \"0\") )); then\n    BTC_TREND=\"📉\"\nfi\n\n# Format stock lines\nSTOCK_LINES=\"\"\nfor symbol in NVDA MSFT GOOGL INTC META AMD; do\n    PRICE=$(echo \"$STOCK_DATA\" | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('$symbol',{}).get('price',0))\")\n    CHANGE=$(echo \"$STOCK_DATA\" | python3 -c \"import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print(d.get('$symbol',{}).get('change_pct',0))\")\n    \n    if (( $(echo \"$CHANGE >= 0\" | bc -l 2>/dev/null || echo \"1\") )); then\n        TREND=\"📈\"\n    else\n        TREND=\"📉\"\n    fi\n    \n    STOCK_LINES+=\"• $symbol $PRICE ($TREND $(printf \"%.2f\" \"$CHANGE\")%)\"\n    STOCK_LINES+=$'\\n'\ndone\n\n# Create formatted message\ncat > \"$MESSAGE_FILE\" << EOF\n📅 $DATE\n\n📈 Crypto\n• Bitcoin: \\$$BTC_PRICE ($BTC_TREND $(printf \"%.2f\" \"$BTC_CHANGE\")%)\n\n💹 Tech Stocks\n$STOCK_LINES\n⭐ Top 10 GitHub Trending Repos\n$(echo \"$GH_DATA\")\n\nHave a productive day! 🤝\nEOF\n\necho \"Message generated: $MESSAGE_FILE\"\n\n# Send via Telegram using message tool\n# This requires the message tool to be available in the environment\nif command -v message >/dev/null 2>&1; then\n    message send --target \"$TELEGRAM_TARGET\" --channel telegram --text \"$(cat $MESSAGE_FILE)\"\n    echo \"Sent via message tool\"\nelse\n    echo \"Message tool not available, message saved to $MESSAGE_FILE\"\nfi\n\necho \"[$DATE] Daily ping completed successfully\" >> \"$LOG_FILE\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772497672265}}
