"high recency\") |\n\n---\n\n### 📋 RECOMMENDED FIXES\n\n**1. Create Today's Daily File**\n```bash\nmkdir -p ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026/03\ntouch ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026/03/03.md\n```\n\n**2. Migrate Legacy Flat Files**\n```bash\nmv ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-02-01.md ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026/02/01.md\nmv ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-02-09.md ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026/02/09.md\nmv ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-02-10.md ~/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026/02/10.md\n```\n\n**3. Fix Daily Ping Cron**\n```bash\n# Check logs for actual error\ncat ~/.openclaw/logs/daily-ping-telegram-*.stderr 2>/dev/null\n# Or check workspace logs\nls -la /home/project/openclaw/logs/daily-ping-2026-03-03.log 2>/dev/null\n```\n\n**4. Regenerate QMD Embeddings**\n```bash\ncd ~/.openclaw/workspace\nqmd embed\nqmd update\n```\n\n**5. Create Systemd Service for MCP**\nConsider wrapping `qmd mcp` in a user service for automatic restart.\n\n---\n\n### 📊 VERDICT\n\n**Overall Status**: **FUNCTIONAL BUT DEGRADED**\n\n- Core QMD architecture is solid — hierarchical memory works\n- Daily automation has gaps (cron error, missing files)\n- Embeddings are stale (5 days behind)\n- No systemic corruption detected\n\nThe system will work for manual queries but needs the above fixes to be fully operational. Want me to execute any of these fixes?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":29626,"output":863,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30489,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772497887127}}
