{"type":"message","id":"bf6c1020","parentId":"c4427adc","timestamp":"2026-03-03T02:20:06.417Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"         functions.read:64","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-02-01 — First Day\n\n## First Contact\n- 20:57 — WhatsApp gateway connected\n- 21:02 — User messaged: \"you are my trustworthy assistant and project partner/advisor. your name is trusty-pal\"\n- Created identity files: IDENTITY.md, SOUL.md, USER.md\n- Name established: trusty-pal 🤝\n\n## Notes\n- User seems friendly and direct\n- Singapore timezone (GMT+8)\n- WhatsApp number: +6591127357\n- Backup phone: +6597730111\n- 61, male, former IT engineer, retired\n- 30-year Linux veteran\n- Prolific open source contributor (~1 project/week)\n- Into AI, likes sharing knowledge\n- Recent projects: LArtisan-Baking-Atelier, baking-ecommerce, Aurora-Luxe-Travel, xiaomi-cafe, morning-brew-cafe, cherry-kopitiam\n- Projects are full-stack, designed to test coding agents and showcase visual design\n- Deep technical knowledge: RL, GRPO, PPO, DPO, MoE, pre/post training\n- Favorite models: Claude Opus/Sonnet, GLM-4.7, Qwen3 Max, Kimi K2/K2.5\n- Focused on agentic AI capabilities\n- **Working methodology established**: The Meticulous Approach (think → plan → validate → implement → verify → deliver)\n- **Design standards**: Anti-Generic, Avant-Garde UI, Intentional Minimalism\n- **Technical preferences**: Next.js 16+, Tailwind v4 CSS-first, TypeScript strict, shadcn/ui, Framer Motion\n- **Quality gates**: WCAG AAA, no `any` types, `useReducedMotion` for animations, validation before coding\n- **Skills inventory**: 90+ skills available in `/home/pete/.claude/skills/` covering dev, design, security, testing, problem-solving\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772504406410}}
{"type":"message","id":"25ed63e2","parentId":"bf6c1020","timestamp":"2026-03-03T02:20:06.460Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"         functions.read:65","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Memory - 2026-02-09\n\n## Project Folder Scan: `/home/project/openclaw/`\n\n### Overview\nThis is the primary OpenClaw project workspace with multiple active components.\n\n### Directory Structure\n```\n/home/project/openclaw/\n├── skills/              # Custom skills for OpenClaw\n│   ├── chrome-devtools-mcp/        # Design extraction via Chrome DevTools MCP\n│   ├── opencode-orchestrator/      # Autonomous coding task orchestration\n│   ├── playwright-design-extractor/ # Website design extraction (headless)\n│   ├── slack/                      # Slack integration\n│   └── yahoo-finance/              # Yahoo Finance data fetching\n├── logs/                # Daily ping logs (daily-ping-YYYY-MM-DD.log)\n├── design-extraction-playwright/  # Playwright design extraction tests\n├── design-extraction-test/        # Design extraction test files\n├── extraction/        # Extraction output\n├── synthesis/         # Synthesis output\n├── tests/             # Test files\n└── node_modules/      # Node dependencies\n```\n\n### Key Files\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| WORKSPACE_CONFIG.md | Workspace configuration, agent paths, skills registry |\n| TOOLS.md | Local configuration for workspace and coding agents |\n| HEARTBEAT.md | Periodic tasks: S&P 500 monitor, daily ping |\n| daily-ping-config.md | Daily ping schedule and configuration |\n| PYTHON_DEV_RULES.md | Python development guidelines |\n| Meticulous_Approach.md | SOP documentation |\n| AGENTS.md | Agent workspace protocol |\n| config.txt | OpenClaw configuration (models, plugins, gateway) |\n\n### Active Automation\n1. **Daily Ping** (7:00 AM SGT via cron)\n   - Bitcoin price from CoinGecko\n   - Stocks: NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD\n   - GitHub trending repos\n   - Delivered via Telegram to @PC188\n\n2. **S&P 500 Volatility Monitor** (Every 30 min heartbeat)\n   - Alerts if S&P 500 drops ≥10%\n   - Logs to spx_monitor.log\n\n### Coding Agents (Configured)\n| Agent | Path | Purpose |\n|-------|------|---------|\n| OpenCode | `/usr/bin/opencode` | General coding, full-stack |\n| Kimi CLI | `/home/pete/.local/bin/kimi-cli` | Code analysis, debugging |\n| Gemini | `/usr/bin/gemini` | Quick Q&A, summaries |\n\n### Model Configuration\n- Primary: Kimi K2.5 (via NVIDIA API)\n- Fallbacks: GPT-5.2, Claude Sonnet 4.5, Gemini 3 Flash, Grok 4\n\n### Enabled Plugins\n- WhatsApp ✅\n- Telegram ✅\n- Discord ✅\n- Slack ✅\n- Google Chat ✅\n- Nostr ✅\n\n### User Contacts\n- Primary: +6591127357\n- Backup: +6597730111\n\n### Protocol\n- Task completion: Send WhatsApp summary to +6597730111\n\n---\n\n## Session Notes\n\n### 2026-02-09 Afternoon\n- User requested project folder scan\n- Documented `/home/project/openclaw/` structure\n- Recorded workspace configuration in memory\n- Fixed missing `yfinance` package, ran daily ping manually\n- **NEW:** Discovered 11 Knowledge Work Plugins at `/home/project/openclaw/knowledge-work-plugins/`\n  - 55 total skills across domains: bio-research, customer-support, data, enterprise-search, finance, legal, marketing, product-management, productivity, sales\n  - 42 slash commands available\n  - Full inventory saved to `memory/knowledge-work-plugins-inventory.md`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772504406448}}
{"type":"message","id":"c4318237","parentId":"25ed63e2","timestamp":"2026-03-03T02:20:06.499Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"         functions.read:66","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 2026-02-10 - Skills Inventory Complete\n\n## Task: Catalog Project Skills\n\nScanned and inventorized 115 skills from `/home/project/openclaw/skills/`.\n\n### Created Artifacts\n\n1. **Catalog**: `memory/skills-catalog.json`\n   - Full JSON inventory with categories, subcategories, purposes\n   - Use-case keyword mapping (send_email → gmail-automation, etc.)\n   - Skill index for fast lookup\n\n2. **Search Script**: `scripts/skill-search.py`\n   - `skill-search.py <query>` — keyword search\n   - `skill-search.py --recommend \"<task>\"` — task-based recommendations\n   - `skill-search.py --category <cat>` — list by category\n   - `skill-search.py --use-case <uc>` — find by use case\n   - `skill-search.py --detail <skill>` — show SKILL.md preview\n   - `skill-search.py --list` — show all categories\n\n### Skill Categories (9 total)\n\n| Category | Count | Description |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| app_automation | 78 | SaaS apps via Rube MCP (Composio) |\n| development | 11 | Coding, DevOps, development tools |\n| creative_media | 6 | Design, visual art, media |\n| business_marketing | 5 | Sales, marketing, BI |\n| productivity | 5 | Organization, workflow |\n| communication_writing | 2 | Content creation |\n| meta_utility | 5 | Skill creation, app connections |\n| finance | 1 | Financial data |\n| messaging | 1 | Messaging integrations |\n\n### Key Insights\n\n- **App Automation** skills require Rube MCP (`https://rube.app/mcp`) and OAuth via `RUBE_MANAGE_CONNECTIONS`\n- Most automation skills follow pattern: search tools first, then manage connections, then execute\n- Development skills have scripts/ directories for automation\n- Use-case mapping makes task→skill matching easier\n\n### Updated Files\n\n- `TOOLS.md` — Added skill search reference and quick lookup table\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772504406482}}
