{"type":"message","id":"b9ecf5a4","parentId":"9de6bd4e","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:40:23.199Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"  Now I have a good understanding of both systems:\n\n1. **context-anchor**: A bash-based recovery tool that:\n   - Scans memory files (flat or hierarchical)\n   - Extracts current task, decisions, open loops\n   - Generates a briefing for session recovery\n   - Pure bash, no dependencies\n   - Uses file system operations (find, grep, stat)\n\n2. **QMD**: A semantic search engine that:\n   - Indexes markdown files into SQLite\n   - Creates vector embeddings for semantic search\n   - Supports BM25 + vector hybrid search\n   - Has collections (system, daily, reference, skills, projects)\n   - Runs MCP server for queries\n   - Requires embeddings to be kept up to date\n\nThe integration opportunity is significant. Let me analyze how to combine them:\n\n**Current State:**\n- context-anchor does pattern-based extraction (decisions, todos, etc.)\n- QMD does semantic/vector search\n- They operate independently\n- context-anchor is faster for structured recovery\n- QMD is better for semantic queries\n\n**Integration Strategy:**\n\n1. **Enhanced context-anchor with QMD query capability**\n   - Instead of just grepping for \"Decision:\", use QMD to find semantically similar decision patterns\n   - Add `--semantic` flag to context-anchor that queries QMD for related context\n\n2. **Pre-computed context snapshots**\n   - Create a `context-snapshot.json` that context-anchor generates and QMD indexes\n   - This bridges the gap between the fast bash tool and semantic search\n\n3. **Unified entry point**\n   - Create a wrapper that runs context-anchor first, then QMD queries for deeper context\n   - Priority: context-anchor for structured data, QMD for fuzzy matching\n\n4. **Smart context caching**\n   - context-anchor extracts key patterns → writes to `context/active/*.md`\n   - QMD indexes these active context files\n   \nI see a strategic approach to merging these systems that builds on their complementary strengths. The goal is to create a seamless, multi-layered memory retrieval mechanism that provides both rapid structured access and deep semantic exploration. By allowing context-anchor and QMD to interact dynamically, I can develop a more intelligent memory system that scales with different information retrieval needs.\n\nThe implementation focuses on creating bidirectional interfaces that leverage the unique capabilities of each tool. This means developing query-directed capabilities in context-anchor while enabling pre-computation mechanisms that bridge the","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Now let"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"   functions.read:92","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/pete/.config/qmd/index.yml"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"   functions.exec:93","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"qmd search \"context compaction\" -c reference 2>&1 | head -10","description":"Test QMD context search"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":61868,"output":576,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":62444,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772512769382}}
{"type":"message","id":"59e5ab91","parentId":"b9ecf5a4","timestamp":"2026-03-03T04:40:23.210Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"   functions.read:92","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"global_context: |\n  OpenClaw workspace memory system. \n  Documents are organized hierarchically: system/, projects/, daily/, skills/, reference/.\n  Prioritize recent documents (2026) over older ones unless specifically relevant.\ncollections:\n  system:\n    path: /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/system\n    pattern: \"**/*.md\"\n    context:\n      /: \"System configuration: OpenClaw gateway, auth tokens, model providers, cron jobs\"\n      \"\": \"System configuration: OpenClaw gateway, auth tokens, model providers, cron jobs\"\n      gateway: \"Gateway settings: port 18789, local mode, NVIDIA provider\"\n      cron: Cron job configuration and scheduling\n      config: OpenClaw configuration files and settings\n  projects:\n    path: /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/projects\n    pattern: \"**/*.md\"\n    context:\n      /: \"Active projects: YouTube content, GitHub open source, CRM system\"\n      /youtube/: \"YouTube channel: video ideas, scripts, competitor analysis\"\n      /github/: Open source projects and contributions\n      /crm/: \"Personal CRM: contacts, meetings, follow-ups\"\n  daily:\n    path: /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily\n    pattern: \"**/*.md\"\n    context:\n      \"2026\": Year 2026 sessions - most recent and relevant\n      /: \"Daily raw notes: session transcripts, quick captures, timestamps\"\n      /2026/: Notes from year 2026 - most recent\n      /2026/02/: February 2026 sessions\n      \"\": \"Daily session notes: conversations, decisions, tasks, observations\"\n      2026/02: February 2026 - high recency\n  skills:\n    path: /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/skills\n    pattern: \"**/*.md\"\n    context:\n      /: \"OpenClaw skills: built-in and custom\"\n      /built-in/: Core OpenClaw platform skills\n      /custom/: Custom workspace-specific skills\n  reference:\n    path: /home/pete/.openclaw/workspace/memory/reference\n    pattern: \"**/*.md\"\n    context:\n      /: \"Curated reference: PRD summaries, architecture guides, personas\"\n      \"\": \"Curated reference: personas, architecture, installation guides, insights\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772512823205}}
